        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="88"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                <head>88. Memorandum From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1"
                        >Vance</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1"
                        >Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d88fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Subject File, Box 19, Evening Reports
                        (State): 12/77. Secret. <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> wrote
                        at the top of the memorandum: “Merry Christmas—Cy.” Beneath <persName
                            corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>’s handwritten note, <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote: “cc Cy, J.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-12-23">December 23, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Omitted here is material unrelated to India.]</p>
                <p>6. <hi rend="italic">Indian Nuclear Policy:</hi> Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_DM_1">Desai</persName> reiterated to the Indian Parliament on
                    December 22 that India would not “explode any nuclear device for peaceful
                    purposes or make any nuclear weapons.” He also implied that fuel for the Tarapur
                    reactors would be forthcoming as in the past and said that the matter would be
                    discussed during your visit.</p>
                <p>Commenting on the pending US non-proliferation legislation, the Prime Minister
                    said that if there was any clause in the bill which affected “our self-respect
                    it will not be accepted by us. But I have no control over the United States
                    Congress and I cannot prevent them from passing any legislation.” This
                    underlines the importance of making progress on full scope safeguards during
                    your visit to New Delhi.<note n="2" xml:id="d88fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>’s planned to visit India
                        January 1–3, 1978. In the left-hand margin next to this and the preceding
                        paragraph, <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote:
                        “Good.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is material unrelated to India.]</p>
            </div>
